TextChange: \nIn the end, I prefer cooperation but I still hold my belief that both are equally important and both have their roles in everyones lives.

\nI truly believe one is not necessarily better than the other. They both play hand in hand with eachother and they are both extremely important in life. Without cooperation we would no achieve goals that need to be done. Same with competition if it was removed we would not see the advancments around the world made that we have today. I think both are equally good and both should be utilized for true success in the world.

\nCompetition is also a huge factor to consider when doing a job or living life as well. People compete on many scales such as pay, housing, vehicles and many other things as well. Competition encourages growth, it makes the mind want more than what it has and to do better at what you are doing. For example if you were in a race for a trophy or anothe prize you would be motivated to beat your competition to win the prize and know that you came out on top. Same is true with companies and businesses, competition pushes technology and work to its limits because each company will want to be known as the best because it will bring more customers in and will bring more workers in who have more knowledge and will cooperate within the company to achieve their goals.\n

However if I truly had to choose which would be better I would have to say cooperation. Cooperation is the true reason that humanity has survived to this day, in every way and shape of life we are always cooperating with someone else just to survive. Whether it be at work or at home the job must always be done and we are always doing it with the help of the people around us. Cooperation drives people to help others and to do their best to help all they can. I don't think that the world would be functional without it.
